<h3 id="instruction">Instruction</h3>

<p>Write a program that takes the radius of a sphere (a floating-point number) as input and then outputs the sphere’s:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Diameter (2 × radius)</li>
  <li>Circumference (diameter × π)</li>
  <li>Surface area (4 × π × radius2)</li>
  <li>Volume (4/3 × π × radius3)</li>
</ol>

<p>For convenience, the program can import the math module.</p>

<p>Below is an example of the program input and output:</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Radius <span class="o">=</span> 5

Diameter     : 10.0
Circumference: 31.41592653589793
Surface area : 314.1592653589793
Volume       : 523.5987755982989
</code></pre></div></div>

